      '<h2>Understanding the Basics</h2><p>Proper pool maintenance can extend your pool\'s lifespan by up to 15 years. Many pool owners confuse two critical procedures: completely emptying a pool versus maintaining its drainage system.</p><p><strong>Pool Draining:</strong> This process involves completely emptying your pool of all water. It functions as a complete reset, allowing for major structural work or addressing severe <a href="/resources/why-regular-pool-cleaning-is-essential-in-san-diegos-climate/">water chemistry</a> problems.</p><p><strong>Pool Drain Cleaning:</strong> This service maintains the drainage infrastructure without removing all the water. The focus is ensuring proper flow by eliminating debris and buildup from drains, pipes, and filtration components.</p>',
      '<h2>When Each Service Is Necessary</h2><h3>Draining is appropriate for:</h3><ul><li>Major structural repairs like resurfacing or crack fixing</li><li>Severely imbalanced water chemistry that chemicals cannot correct</li><li>Long-term closures or seasonal shutdowns</li><li>Tile replacement or underwater repairs requiring a dry environment</li></ul><h3>Drain cleaning is appropriate for:</h3><ul><li>Slower drainage or reduced circulation</li><li>Service every 6-12 months depending on usage</li><li>Preparing for peak swimming season</li><li>Debris accumulation around drains despite regular skimming</li><li>Declining water quality despite chemical treatments</li></ul>',
