      '<h2>Preventive Maintenance: The Key to Fewer Drain Problems</h2><h3>Daily Habits That Make a Difference</h3><p>Recommended practices include quick daily skimming, rinsing before swimming, maintaining proper chemical balance, and regularly checking skimmer baskets.</p><h3>Seasonal Maintenance Checklist</h3><p>Spring requires deep cleaning for winter buildup removal; summer demands frequent checks during peak use; fall needs extra vigilance against leaves; winter requires proper winterization.</p><h3>Smart Upgrades Worth Considering</h3><p>Investments include modern anti-clog drain covers, automated skimmers, secondary filter systems, and pool covers reducing debris accumulation.</p>',
